The paper deals with Bayesian inference problems defined on factor graphs, which are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the replica symmetric prediction, which is a concept from statistical physics (cs.DS). The application of the method to a Censored Block Model involves binary erasure channels, which are studied in information theory and communication systems (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with rigorous results for sparse systems, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
